Reasoning: The paper focuses on the analysis of personality traits of developers in software development projects and their relationship with the software artifacts they interact with. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The approach used in the paper involves the automatic recognition of personality traits from e-mails, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the social and technical aspects of software development, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
